Comment: This is a waste of a move. It doesn't help develop any pieces or attack the center of the board. The only thing this move does is prevent the bishop from going to b4 later.
Another waste of tempo. The bishop moved twice for no reason.
I would have played 5...Nxe4 6.Nxe4. and then d5. It gives black a good position. d6 only prevents the dark squared bishop from getting into a better position.
A move that doesen't acomplish anything. Another weak move from white.
That pawn on e4 was just wating to be taken. Oh well.
Attempting a mate on f7. The mate can be stoped many ways.
White wins with a simple mate early in the game. Remember that this game was played in the casual section of the tournament.
